Class EventWaiter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.breadmoirai.bot.waiter.EventWaiter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.dv8tion.jda.core.hooks.EventListener

    public class EventWaiter
extends java.lang.Object
implements net.dv8tion.jda.core.hooks.EventListener

    Original class from EventWaiter.java in Github Project JDA -Utilities created by John Grosh (jagrosh). Modified by Ton Ly (BreadMoirai)

    The EventWaiter is capable of handling specialized forms of Event that must meet criteria not normally specifiable without implementation of an EventListener.

    This is a singleton class accessed through EventWaiter#get

      • waitForEvent

        public <T extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.Event> void waitForEvent(java.lang.Class<T> classType,
                                                                       java.util.function.Predicate<T> action)
        Waits an indefinite amount of time for an Event of the specified type. Then the Event is applied to the Predicate. If the Predicate returns false, the EventWaiter will wait for the next event of the specified type. Otherwise the action is considered satisfied and removed from the EventWaiter.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of Event to wait for
        Parameters:
        classType - The Class of the Event to wait for
        action - A Predicate. Should return true when action is complete, else false if action is not satisfied and should wait for additional events.

      • waitForEvent

        public <T extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.Event> void waitForEvent(java.lang.Class<T> classType,
                                                                       java.util.function.Predicate<T> condition,
                                                                       java.util.function.Consumer<T> action)
        Waits an indefinite amount of time for an Event on which the provided Predicate would return true.

        When this occurs, the provided Consumer will accept and handle using the same Event.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of Event to wait for
        Parameters:
        classType - The Class of the Event to wait for
        condition - A Predicate. Should return true when the Event should be passed to the action, else false if the EventWaiter continue waiting event.
        action - This is a Consumer that is run when the condition is satisfied.

      • waitForEvent

        public <T extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.Event> void waitForEvent(java.lang.Class<T> eventType,
                                                                       java.util.function.Predicate<T> action,
                                                                       long timeout,
                                                                       java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit,
                                                                       java.lang.Runnable timeoutAction)
        Waits a predetermined amount of time for an Event that is of the specified eventType and uses the provided Predicate action. If action returns true, it will be removed from this EventWaiter. If action returns false, Events of the same type will continue to be passed to it.

        If by the time it times out and action has not yet returned true, the timeoutAction will be executed.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of Event to wait for
        Parameters:
        eventType - The Class of the Event to wait for
        action - The Predicate that is run with the Event, returning true if it is satisfied
        timeout - The maximum amount of time to wait for
        unit - The TimeUnit measurement of the timeout
        timeoutAction - The Runnable to run if the time runs out before a correct Event is thrown

      • waitForEvent

        public <T extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.Event> void waitForEvent(java.lang.Class<T> eventType,
                                                                       java.util.function.Predicate<T> condition,
                                                                       java.util.function.Consumer<T> action,
                                                                       long timeout,
                                                                       java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit,
                                                                       java.lang.Runnable timeoutAction)
        Waits a predetermined amount of time for an Event that returns true when tested with the provided Predicate condition. Then the Event is passed to the provided Predicate action. If action returns true, the action will be removed. If the action returns false, it will continue to wait for additional Events.

        Once the this times out, if condition has ever returned true, the timeoutAction will not be run. If condition has never returned true, the timeoutAction will be run.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of Event to wait for
        Parameters:
        eventType - The Class of the Event to wait for
        condition - The Predicate that tests the Event
        action - The Predicate that is run when condition returns true, returning true if it is satisfied
        timeout - The maximum amount of time to wait for
        unit - The TimeUnit measurement of the timeout
        timeoutAction - The Runnable to run if the time runs out before a correct Event is thrown
